As part of Cavs Youth Sports Summer Series, Cavs Academy will host in-person Skills Training Clinics, presented by Gatorade, at Rocket Mortgage FieldHouse this summer.
Skills Training Clinics are $50 and include an exclusive dri-fit shooting shirt, Spalding basketball and ticket to a future Cavaliers home game. Clinics run on Mondays, Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays starting on Monday, July 20 and ending on Thursday, August 6. The 9-11 a.m. session is open to ages 7-9 and the 1-3 p.m. session is open to ages 10-17.
To enroll and for information on safety guidelines, visit cavsyouth.com/summerseries.

post_text:
Juneteenth is celebrated to symbolize the end of slavery in the United States.

It is held on June 19, to mark the date in 1865 when Union soldiers rode into Galveston, Texas and told a group of slaves that the Civil War had ended and they were now free. President Abraham Lincoln had signed the Emancipation Proclamation two years earlier, but news of that document and of the end of the war traveled slowly.

post_text:
Hello Families,

Mindfulness and the Arts: Nature Walk Mandala

Creating Mandalas can be a form of art therapy that can reduce anxiety, tension and overall stress.

Mandalas are circles contained within a square and arranged into sections that are all organized around a single, central point.

Mandalas can be found in nature:
Snowflakes, Flowers, Cobwebs, and in Tree Rings.
Look outside for natural materials.
Make Sure To Look For a Variety of Objects.
Group Them by Object.
Start Building Your Nature Walk Mandalas.

Click on Link to watch a quick video to get started on your nature walk mandalas: https://youtu.be/ol3zK3YFVBA

Happy Creating,
Mrs.Thomas
Art Teacherüë©üèΩ‚Äçüé®

Mindfulness and the Arts üé≠

Color with Mrs. Thomas Today! You can use coloring book pages or draw your own pictures on a black sheet of paper and color.

The benefits of coloring pages: 1) Self expression - coloring on a blank "canvas" (piece of paper), is a way for children and adults alike to express themselves. You can tell a lot about the way a person is feeling by the images that they draw, the colors that they use, etc.

The humming bird illustration is one of my personal artworks that I used a blank canvas to draw and color using ink and color pencils.

Mrs. Thomas
Art Teacherüë©üèΩ‚Äçüé®

post_text: Good morning families, we are continuing to monitor the coronavirus situation and make adjustments in the best interest of student and staff safety. To help prevent the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19), we are cancelling all scheduled field trips and prohibiting spectator participation at extra-curricular events. If you have specific questions about an event, feel free to call the school or email the front office. Thank you for your understanding. We will continue to post updates as they come.

post_text: I know many are concerned about the Coronavirus (COVID-19) and have been asking about the plans for our school. Our staff is working with our school officials to coordinate efforts and ensure the safety of our staff and students with minimal disruption to effective instruction and school operation. Visit our website or Facebook page for the most up to date information.
